tags.description: This is a scenic campsite in northern Fiordland that is good for larger vehicles.
tags.name: Cascade Creek Campsite

tags.description: This is a standard campsite in the Queenstown/Wakatipu area. Camp within scenic rocky natural features on terraces around an old cemetery and school. Bike, walk, tramp or hunt to explore the area.
tags.name: Skippers Campsite

tags.description: This is a walk-in, Great Walk campsite on the Routeburn Track, Fiordland National Park. Bookings required in the Great Walks season.
tags.name: Lake Mackenzie Campsite

tags.description: Just below point 1912. Operated by mountainhut.nz, but 2 spaces reserved for tramping parties as part of agreement with DOC.
tags.name: Kelly's Hut

tags.description: This is a walk-in, Great Walk campsite in the Route Burn valley, on the Routeburn Track in Mt Aspiring National Park. Bookings required in the Great Walks season.
tags.name: Routeburn Flats Campsite

tags.description: Park up near the shores of Diamond Lake, on the edge of Mt Aspiring National park. Explore the area around Paradise and along the Dart and Rees tramping tracks. Swim, fish or go kayaking.
tags.name: Diamond Lake Campsite
Upper Caples Hut
tags.operator: Southern Lakes New Zealand Deerstalkers Association

tags.description: Camp on a river delta at the outlet of Twelve-Mile Creek near the shores of Lake Wakatipu. Go boating, swimming and fishing or enjoy the walking and mountain biking tracks. Regenerating forest surrounds the campsite.
tags.name: Twelve Mile Delta Campsite

tags.description: This is a scenic campsite in the Queenstown/Wakatipu area. This is a peaceful place beside a small lake. Go boating, swimming, fishing or canoeing on the lake. Walk or mountain bike from Moke Lake to Lake Dispute (2 hour walk).
tags.name: Moke Lake Campsite

tags.description: Camp on the shores of Lake Wakatipu, New Zealand’s longest lake. Explore the area along the Caples or the Greenstone tramping tracks. Swim, kayak, fish or go boating on the lake, or enjoy the scenery.
tags.name: Kinloch Campsite

tags.description: This is a scenic campsite in the Queenstown/Wakatipu area. Camp beside the Routeburn River. Walk to Lake Sylvan via the bridge or day walk the start of the Routeburn Great Walk. Fish in the river (fly fishing only).
tags.name: Sylvan Campsite
